    <!-- Legal info -->
    <string name="legal_title">Legal information</string>
    <string name="legal_about_title">About this app</string>
    <string name="legal_about_text">radioMii is a free and open-source software (FOSS) project created by hobby enthusiasts whose sole motivation is to build useful apps for the community. This app is developed on a non-commercial basis. We have no commercial interest and no interest whatsoever in collecting, processing, or monetizing your data.</string>
    <string name="legal_privacy_title">Privacy &amp; data usage</string>
    <string name="legal_privacy_text">radioMii does not track, collect, or store any personal or user-related data. No analytics, no telemetry, no user profiles.\n\nThe only data stored is your list of favorite stations, which is kept locally on your device. If you choose to back up or export your favorites to Google Drive, that transfer is initiated and controlled solely by you. No data is sent to the developers of radioMii at any time.</string>
    <string name="legal_third_party_title">Third-party services &amp; network access</string>
    <string name="legal_third_party_text">radioMii retrieves station information from the community-maintained radio-browser.info database. When you browse or search for stations, your device connects to radio-browser.info servers, which may be able to see your IP address and request metadata.\n\nWhen you play a radio station, your device connects directly to the stream server operated by the respective station provider. These third-party servers may also be able to see your IP address and other connection details.\n\nThe developers of radioMii have no control over these third-party services.</string>
    <string name="legal_disclaimer_title">Content disclaimer</string>
    <string name="legal_disclaimer_text">radioMii does not host, curate, or editorially control any content. All radio stations are played via stream links sourced from the radio-browser.info database.\n\nSome streams may broadcast content that is restricted by age, subject to licensing requirements, or prohibited by the laws of your country or jurisdiction. The user is solely responsible for ensuring that their use of the app complies with all applicable local laws and regulations.</string>
    <string name="legal_no_warranty_title">No warranty</string>
    <string name="legal_no_warranty_text">radioMii is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or implied. The developers make no guarantees regarding the availability, accuracy, or reliability of the app or any third-party content accessed through it. Use of the app is entirely at your own risk.</string>

